%% Data Science Pipelines (Tekton) - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as User/Client
    participant Route as OpenShift Route<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant OAuth as OAuth Proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant UI as ds-pipeline-ui<br/>3000/TCP HTTP
    participant API as ds-pipeline API Server<br/>8888/TCP HTTP REST<br/>8887/TCP gRPC
    participant MySQL as MySQL/MariaDB<br/>3306/TCP
    participant MinIO as MinIO/S3<br/>9000/TCP HTTP
    participant TektonAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant PA as Persistence Agent
    participant SWF as Scheduled Workflow Controller
    participant MW as metadata-writer
    participant MLMD as metadata-grpc<br/>8080/TCP gRPC
    participant Envoy as metadata-envoy<br/>9090/TCP gRPC

    Note over Client,MinIO: Flow 1: Pipeline Submission and Execution

    Client->>Route: POST pipeline upload<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS
    Route->>OAuth: Reencrypt TLS<br/>HTTPS/8443
    OAuth->>UI: Session Cookie<br/>HTTP/3000
    UI->>API: Submit Pipeline<br/>HTTP/8888, Bearer Token
    API->>MySQL: Store pipeline definition<br/>MySQL/3306, User/Pass
    API->>MinIO: Store pipeline artifacts<br/>HTTP/9000, AccessKey/SecretKey
    API->>TektonAPI: Create PipelineRun CR<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token
    TektonAPI-->>API: PipelineRun created

    Note over PA,API: Flow 2: Pipeline Run Persistence

    PA->>TektonAPI: Watch PipelineRuns/TaskRuns<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token
    TektonAPI-->>PA: PipelineRun status updates
    PA->>API: Persist run status<br/>HTTP/8888

    Note over SWF,TektonAPI: Flow 3: Scheduled Workflow Execution

    SWF->>TektonAPI: Watch ScheduledWorkflow CRs<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token
    TektonAPI-->>SWF: ScheduledWorkflow events
    SWF->>TektonAPI: Create PipelineRun<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token

    Note over MW,MySQL: Flow 4: ML Metadata Tracking

    MW->>TektonAPI: Watch PipelineRuns<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token
    TektonAPI-->>MW: PipelineRun completion
    MW->>MLMD: Write execution metadata<br/>gRPC/8080
    MLMD->>MySQL: Store MLMD records<br/>MySQL/3306, User/Pass

    Note over Client,Envoy: Flow 4b: MLMD Client Access

    Client->>Envoy: Query metadata<br/>gRPC/9090
    Envoy->>MLMD: Forward request<br/>gRPC/8080
    MLMD-->>Envoy: Metadata response
    Envoy-->>Client: Response
